''Circa'' [[1357 DR]], the [[Panthers of Xi]] [[ninja]] controlled the northern mountains between [[Xi]] and the Malu River in the east.

Somewhere, high in the mountains, likely near the town of [[Pan (town)|Pan]] in the west, the yakuza [[wu jen]] [[No Ziar]] claimed a keep, in which he stored his hidden wealth.

A handsome breed of "birdmen" ruled the tallest peaks of the mountains. They were enigmatic to the folk of Koryo. They were later theorized to be [[Hengeyokai|crane hengeyokai]], forming a larger-than-normal flock.<ref>{{Cite dragon/404/Ecology of the Hengeyokai|3}}
